# Modulo de Tickets e Compras

## Entidades

- `Ticket`: id, location, event_id, price (string decimal), status (available | sold | reserved)
- `Purchase`: id, customer_id, purchase_date, total_amount (string decimal), status (paid | pending | cancelled)

## Arquivos principais

- Entities: `src/domain/entities/Ticket.ts`, `src/domain/entities/Purchase.ts`
- Repositories: `ITicketRepository`, `IPurchaseRepository` + implementacoes em `data/repositories/`
- Services: `TicketService`, `PurchaseService`
- Hooks: `useCreateTickets`, `usePurchaseTickets`, `useTicketsByEvent`, `useMyPurchases`
- UI: `PurchaseTicketDialog`, `src/routes/_authenticated/tickets.tsx`

## Endpoints

- `POST /events/:eventId/tickets` - Criar tickets (partner)
- `GET /events/:eventId/tickets` - Listar tickets de um evento
- `POST /purchases` - Comprar tickets (customer, envia ticket_ids + card_token)
- `GET /purchases` - Listar compras do customer

## Cache keys

- `["events", eventId, "tickets"]` - tickets de um evento
- `["events", eventId, "tickets", "available-count"]` - contagem disponivel
- `["my-purchases"]` - compras do customer

## Diferenca por role

- Partner: cria eventos com tickets (num_tickets + price no form)
- Customer: ve ingressos disponiveis, compra via dialog, acessa "Meus Ingressos"

Para detalhes completos, consulte `docs/tickets-module.md`.
